      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## @tags — tag people and contexts in your tasks\n\nType `@` inside a task to tag a person or any context — e.g. `talk to @matyas, then send docs`.\n\n- **Autocomplete** — typing `@` opens a filtered dropdown of tags you already use. `Tab`/`Shift+Tab` or `↑`/`↓` to move the selection, `Enter` to insert. The tag lands with the cursor right after it (no trailing space), so `@matyas,` flows naturally.\n- **Sidebar entries** — every tag with open tasks appears in the left rail below your lists, with a live incomplete count, sorted by how many open tasks reference it. Click one to see all its tasks.\n- **Tag search** — a search starting with `@` matches by tag. Partial and word-start matches work: `@olch` finds `@piotrOlchawa`.\n- **Readable display** — `@piotrOlchawa` shows as \"@Piotr Olchawa\" in the rail and capitalized inline. Accented letters fold to ASCII on save and casing is unified, so a person is one tag no matter how you type them.\n- **Drag onto a tag** in the rail to add it to a task.\n\nTags live inline in your `todo.txt` using the standard `@context` convention, so they stay compatible with other todo.txt tools.\n",
      "downloadCount": 5,
