      "author": "2easy",
      "description": "## macOS Dock badge\n\n- Optional native red badge on Obsidian's Dock icon counting your **overdue tasks** (uncompleted, `due` before today). **Off by default** — enable it in settings.\n- Second toggle, **\"Badge includes tasks due today\"** (on by default when the badge is enabled): counts due-today + overdue, making the badge match the Today view's number — the Reminders/Things/Todoist convention. Turn it off for strict \"only what I'm late on\".\n- Zero hides the badge entirely; completed tasks never count.\n- Stays fresh without opening the Nudge pane: recomputed on startup, on every `todo.txt` change (including external edits), on settings changes, and when the date rolls over — a minute tick catches midnight and overnight sleep/wake.\n- Bonus fix from the rollover tick: open Nudge views now re-render when the day changes, so the **Today view rolls over at midnight** instead of showing yesterday's state until the next edit.\n- Disabling the plugin (or a read error) clears the badge rather than leaving a stale number.\n\n## Housekeeping\n\n- Type-safe Electron access for the badge and popout-safe `requestAnimationFrame`, resolving all `typescript-eslint` warnings.\n- ESLint setup mirroring the Obsidian plugin-review linter (`npm run lint`): typescript-eslint type-checked rules + `eslint-plugin-obsidianmd`.\n",
      "downloadCount": 3,
