      "author": "2easy",
      "description": "## Fuzzy search across all lists\n\n- New magnifying-glass button in the panel header (left of **+**) that widens into an inline search input, or open it with the new configurable hotkey.\n- Live fuzzy matching from the 2nd character on, re-ranked on every keystroke. Below 2 characters the previous view stays put.\n- Searches item text **and** link URLs — links are cleaned before matching (protocol/`www.`/query stripped, percent-decoded, slugs split into words), so `blood angels` finds `…/how-to-paint-blood-angels`.\n- **Results** view: incomplete matches on top by relevance, all completed matches in the dimmed section below — shown by default, with the eye toggle hiding them independently of the other views.\n- Matched characters are highlighted in the item text; when the match landed in the URL, the row's link button gets the same highlight.\n- Every result shows its list tag(s); clicking a tag jumps to that list. Rows stay fully interactive (complete, inline edit, delete, due date, copy), and results can be dragged onto a rail list or Today. Copy-list works over the results in all three formats.\n- Exit with **Esc** or the **✕** inside the input to return to the previously selected view (filters intact); clicking a rail list also exits. In Results, **+** returns to the previous view and starts an inline add there.\n\n## Configurable search hotkey\n\n- New setting with the same click-and-press recorder as the new-task hotkey (e.g. record `Cmd+F`). Unset by default.\n- Honored only while the Nudge view is the active pane, and it overrides Obsidian's own binding for that combo (e.g. find-in-note for `Cmd+F`).\n",
